HEADWORD: Breasthook
<hw>Breast"hook`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A thick piece of timber in the form of a knee, placed across the
stem of a ship to strengthen the fore part and unite the bows on each
side.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Breasting</ent>⟦br⟧
